	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Always state the purpose of your "raid" first and agree on loot rules. Tell people who join late what is going on and what they can expect ... it's only fair and that is what you would want. ALSO ... PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE ... make sure that if you join a group you ASK what the loot rules are so there are no hard feelings afterwards.<br />
<br />
And now on my favorite subject ... WHat is up with Master Looters (ML's) now-a-days ? Do they really think that the whole group is there for them to abscond with the parties whole take for the afternoon ? Do they really think that we don't know how much a darkwood bow or a shimmering clover are worth as VT (Vendor Trash) ? Why is it that when the ML has to leave he never comes back with a share of plat for everyone ? Is the newest breed of ML just kids who have to run to the dinner tableand as such the reason "Mom's calling me for dinner" or "Dad wants to use the computer" allows them to keep 3 or 4 hundred plat to themselves. No wonder these guys have such UBER gear and I am so damned poor.</font></p>
	
