	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Most of the pickup groups I'm in are run fairly. Everyone gets a fair share of the loot with the cleric getting a raw, blue or regular diamond to pay for peridots. I did have an occurence in PoJ where an enchanter named Qlain took off with 3-400 plat worth of items because "his mom wanted him off the computer."He declared himself ML from the start and said he'd split at the end. I knew right away what it would amount to, he'd end up with a good chunk of cash and the other 5 ppl would get screwed. I go LD and come back, group except him are still there and they told me he had to go. I asked if he had split the loots, 2-3 ppl said Nope and had another similar occurence in PoV where a ranger thought it'd be funny to watch ppl fly for loots as he ninja'd them before the mob hit the ground. Though with the guild I'm applying to, nothing on raids gets looted unless you have the authority to do so. Gives no room for BS or miscommunication.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
